These support blocks are arranged in a triangular shape.

   **Structure 2 (on the right):** This structure has a base of a horizontal rectangular block (likely #8 from the dictionary) positioned underneath a horizontal rectangular block (likely #8) on top of which is a vertical rectangular block (likely #6 or #10).   The right and left sides of the structure are supported by a slanted (truncated) rectangular block (likely #1) and a vertical rectangular block (likely #6 or #10). A triangular block (likely #13) sits on top. A small square block (likely #5) is placed at the center top. Finally, a small rectangular block (likely #5)  is placed on the top right of the structure.
